text: Litoria chrisdahli is a frog from Papua New Guinea. It lives in the Sepik Basin. This frog has a spike on the end of its nose. Scientists say it is related to Litoria prora and Litoria humboldtorum but it is smaller and smaller flaps of skin on its legs. It also sounds different when it calls out. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Litoria chrisdahli
